    {
      "id": "0c863c69067c00bf04c0ce2c7bbc2af9b61e0231",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-28 01:18:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI'm happy to see Old cruft like this being removed from the build system. There is probably a bunch more cleanup that could be done along these lines (e.g. checks in the code for kernel > 2.5.99 or similar) bit every bit helps. \n\nThat said, it looks like this patch had a build problem, so I'll have to re-review it when a new version is uploaded.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "de29db65b6336f9cc829d9d367435114ed4a4a02",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-28 15:21:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nGlad to know this type of patch is well accepted. I will go through and see what else I can remove based on the kernel > 2.5.99 suggestion and resubmit.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "36e3f15f77b25247bb3aca3ac4691268e1e3be70",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-28 16:01:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLooking into the build failure a bit more.. It fails when trying to apply the ldiskfs patches. Is the 2.6-rhel6.series ldiskfs patch series supposed to apply cleanly to the ubuntu 10.04 kernel sources? Is ldiskfs supposed to be getting built on ubuntu at all? I thought it was only the client (i.e no ldiskfs), but I could be misunderstanding something..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "733360743d45a1d7edfdf3ca5327680dc50ff23b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-28 19:22:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nFYI, if this patch is a functional stand-alone cleanup, I don't insist that all of the potential < 2.6.0 code is cleaned up in this patch.  Having a bunch of smaller independent patches (e.g. each submitted from a separate branch) makes it easier to inspect and test them individually, and if any changes are needed in one it won't block others from landing.\n\nAs for ldiskfs, the patch series determination is quite simple.  Basically it checks the kernel version, and in a couple of cases it checks the distro (e.g. sles11 and rhel6).\n\nWe definitely don't have Ubuntu server support, so that is  a mistake.  Normally, the configure code detects an unpatched kernel and disables server support entirely, but I don't know much about how Lustre is built on Ubuntu.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "59fefcaebd64cce7ff0731f61b1c7a340cc281b1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-29 19:51:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: No score\n\nOk, yeah I had thought Ubuntu wasn't supported on the server. I'm unsure why it tried to build the ldiskfs module here..\n\nAnd yes, I believe this patch can serve as a stand alone patch to remove some of the old cruft.\n\nI'll try to reproduce the build issue in an Ubuntu VM and see if I can determine what the issue is. Im completely unfamiliar with building on Ubuntu.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
